A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Georgia Teacher Leader Consortium; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia Teacher Leader Consortium (GTLC) is a dedicated network of
4 National Board Certified teachers and educators who work to enhance the teaching
5 profession in Georgia; and
6 WHEREAS, the GTLC has established a nonprofit organization to support educators,
7 increase the number of National Board Certified teachers in Georgia, and ensure that every
8 child has access to accomplished educators, regardless of zip code; and
9 WHEREAS, as a proud affiliate of the National Board for Professional Teaching Standards,
10 the GTLC actively collaborates with local legislators on educational initiatives that align with
11 its mission of excellence in teaching and learning; and
12 WHEREAS, the GTLC is led by an esteemed board of educators, including Dr. Heavenly
13 Montgomery, president and founder; Dr. Elletta Denson, vice president; Deanna Rogers,
14 executive director; Natalia Rachel, director of STEM education; Dr. Shannon Flounnory,
15 executive director of leadership programs; Charla Fields, director of professional learning;
