16 Kamasia Wright, director of communications; Altames Larkins, director of instructional
17 efficacy; and Kartisha Bentley, school leadership advisor; and
18 WHEREAS, the dedication and expertise of these leaders have contributed significantly to
19 the advancement of teacher advocacy, instructional excellence, and professional growth
20 opportunities for educators across Georgia; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this outstanding organization be
22 appropriately honored.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body recognize and commend the Georgia Teacher Leader Consortium
25 for its invaluable contributions to the teaching profession and its continued efforts to support
26 and advocate for educators in Georgia as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
28 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
29 Georgia Teacher Leader Consortium.
